        <div id="e0" style="position:absolute;left:1;top:0;width:998;height:78;"><!--$img %ImageAssetImpl:/images/generic_dusk_header.jpg$--><img src="sitebuilder/images/generic_dusk_header-998x78.jpg" width="998" height="78" alt=""></div>        <div id="e1" style="position:absolute;left:1;top:78;width:998;height:44;"><img src="images/generic_dusk_search_bar_background_tile.gif" width="998" height="44" alt=""></div>        <div id="e2" style="position:absolute;left:150;top:25;width:730;height:40;"><span class="text"><font color="#D4A84B" size="6"><span style="font-size:30px;line-height:35px;">Dojo Rules - Protocol<br/></span></font></span>        </div>
        <div id="e3" style="position:absolute;left:155;top:175;width:675;height:787;"><span class="text"><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">When the class begins, students will line up facing </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">shomen</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> (the front of the </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">), in </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">musubi dachi</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, according to rank, with <br/>the higher ranking member to your left. </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Sensei</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> will take a position in front of the class and sit in </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">zazen</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> (formal seated <br/>position). The ranking student will announce:<br><br></span></font><ul style="padding:0;margin:0px 0px 0px 40px;;"><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Seiza!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> &nbsp;This is the command to sit in the formal seated position. Students will kneel, in order of rank, until everyone <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">is seated. You will be </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">instructed about these procedures on your first day by a senior student.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Mokuso!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> This is a brief period of meditation, self reflection or personal preparation. You close your eyes, breathe in <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">slowly through your </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">nose </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">and then exhale slowly through your mouth. Remain still and quiet.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> Mokuso Yame!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> Open your eyes and remain quietly seated.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Shomen ni Rei!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> Bow to the front of the dojo. </span></font><b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Please note</span></font></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">: This has no religious significance. It is only showing <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">respect to Masters </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Funakoshi, </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Nakayama and Okazaki.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Sensei ni Rei!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> Bow to </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei</span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">. You should say, </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">osu!</span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, and maintain your bow until</span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> sensei</span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> finishes bowing. When you <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">rise, you must wait for </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">the </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">person to your left to stand </span></font><b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">before</span></font></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> you stand. Once everyone is standing, you may move to <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">your position on the floor.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font></ul><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br>Once everyone is in position, a </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sempai</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> will lead the class in warm up. Proper respect and attitude will be expected at all <br/>times. You are in class to train. Interruptions and misbehaving will not be tolerated! It is not only rude and disrespectful, it is <br/>also dangerous. Safety is our first concern. If you need to leave the floor for any reason, you must have</span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> sensei&#8217;s</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> permission. <br/>There are no breaks for drinks or to use the restroom; do these things before class starts. If it is excessively hot or the <br/>training has been very difficult, </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei</span></font></i><b><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> may</span></font></b><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> allow a break. If so, be quick and return promptly.<br><br>Your karate training will consist mainly of three parts, </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">kihon, kata</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> and </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">kumite</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">. Never ask </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, &#8220;What are we going to do <br/>today?&#8221; It is considered rude and impolite to ask. You are there to do whatever you are asked to do. Ideally, we will work on <br/>all aspects of karate in each class; however, this may not always be the case. Be prepared for anything. Have your gloves <br/>and mouth guard with you for each class. Training includes:<br><br></span></font><ul style="padding:0;margin:0px 0px 0px 40px;;"><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Kihon</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> - These are the basics of karate. It includes all blocks, strikes, punches, kicks and stances.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Kata</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> - The </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">kata</span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, or forms, are a series of blocks, strikes, kicks, punches and stances combined to simulate an <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">attack by several </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">opponents. </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Every </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">kata </span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">begins with a block to foster the idea of karate as a method of self-defense, <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">not attack.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Kumite</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> - This is sparring or fighting. </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Kumite </span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">is geared specifically to each level of training and gets progressively <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">more intense as the </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">student </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">increases in rank.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font></ul><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br>At the end of class, we often have cool-down stretches, partner stretches or, in the case of the children&#8217;s classes, &#8220;animal <br/>exercises.&#8221; These last exercises are done when we have extra time and are designed to build muscle and stamina in the <br/>children, most of whom are too young to be lifting weights. They consist of twelve sets of movements, most named after the <br/>animal they resemble. The group includes: monkey, bear, seal, cricket, duck walk, duck hop, frog, spider, bunny, crab, <br/>elephant, and military crawl. We also do suicide sprints, jogging, and other cardiovascular exercises in the</span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">.<br><br>The command to line up signals the end of the class. Students are to run and line up in </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">musubi dachi</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">. You will line up in <br/>the same order as you did at the beginning of class. The ranking </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sempai </span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">will announce:<br><br></span></font><ul style="padding:0;margin:0px 0px 0px 40px;;"><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Seiza! </span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Sit in the same manner as in the beginning of class.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Mokuso!</span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> Close your eyes and clear your mind.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Mokuso Yame! </span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Open your eyes.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Dojo Kun! </span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">This is the reciting of the dojo rules aloud. Senior students are expected to know it both in English and <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Japanese.</span></font><b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> NOTE</span></font></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">: &nbsp;The </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Dojo </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Kun will be listed later in these rules.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Shomen ni Rei! </span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Bow to the front.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"><br></span></font><li style="line-height:0px;color:#000000;"><b><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Sensei ni Rei! </span></font></i></b><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Bow to </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei </span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">and say, </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Domo arigato gozaimashita</span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, or Thank you very much. </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Sensei </span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">will stand and <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">signal the </span></font><i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sempai </span></font></i><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">to </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">stand. You will wait to stand until the person on your left stands. Everyone then bows again, <br/></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">standing, and leaves quickly and quietly.<br/></span></font></ul></span>        </div>
